  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is designed to test if there is any correlation between the glucose levels in the
      postoperatory period and the length of hospital stay.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The stress hyperglycemia commonly observed in the postoperatory period, there have been
      several studies to assess if there is benefit of having a strict glucose control or not.

      This study will assess if there is correlation between the glucose levels measured
      continuously with the length of the stay in the hospital.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
